<br>
am just telling what I do, even though i do not know, if you can do better....<br>
<br>
First to my equipment:<br>
- I have 2 prepoisened 2h swords on me (disease and snare)<br>
- I have my main set of 1h sword and left axe prepoisoned with DoT and debuff<br>
- I have a backup set of 1h sword and 1h left axe prepoisoned with DoT and debuff<br>
- i have df bought helmet instead of epic helm on, I use df bought sleeves (crit mod) on first hit.<br>
--<br>
<br>
When i pick a victim in a group of enemies (like one standing on top of mg, the others standing at bottom), I use my 2h sword, with disease on it. I line up normally in front and use my hotkeys 2 (perf), 3 switch to 1h sword, 4 stick, 5 switch to left axe, 6 Creeping death<br>
I wait if CD is successfull. If it was successfull I hit 7 for SS and switch to my melee-la hotkey bar. The key here is disease to stop heals. If it doesnt go too well, i jump to other side of mg and stealth asap to the woods to hide from anyone with TS, in any other case I try to get some more hits off, till it is time to jump to safety. In case you did well and luck was with you, you get your rps upon restealth, when poison DoT finished your victim =P. The key here is some luck on perf (drives enemies mad, when you pick em one by one =P )<br>
<br>
When I pick archers or exspect a 1vs1 or 1vs2, I use my snare prepoisoned 2h sword. Either do the combo mentioned, or do your perf, sprint anead of your enemy and restealth. I seldomly use the last option, as it gives your victim time to think, to prepare and yell for mates. Whereas, when you hit him and stay on him, he messes around with his keyboard, trying to enter combat mode asap, leaving no time to call for help. By the time he fights back, he already has: snare, DoT and debuff on him. I switch to my epic sleeves (its like a heal by its const bonus and I do not need the crit mod from df sleeves any more) and to timourous drakulv gloves (for la bonus. yeah, only 3 pts more la and 7 str more, but imho worth it). By the time I have the armour switched, I already switch weapons to my 2nd set of sword/la, to reapply that nifty DoT/debuff combo.<br>
<br>
If my enemy looks too strong, I open battle from stealth with my necklace (2 charges of DoT) and do perf asap thereafter.<br>
<br>
Should i fight a moving cloth caster, I no longer perf: I simply switch to my two 1h weapons, sprint to him and start with la styles, pressing sprint if he moves too fast.<br>
<br>
If the caster is standing, I of course perf him as needed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  . <p>--- <BR>
